Hello, I’m trying to do some planning work before purchasing an omio tube fixture, but unfortunately there’s a dimension missing from the drawings. I need the distances between the bolt holes used to bolt to the nut strip, and the edges of the fixture (see red dimension in attached image). If anyone has a model they can give me, or even a tube fixture and a pair of calipers to measure it themselves, I’d appreciate it. (Also I did email WCP support, but I figured I’d try all my options)

We’re locked out of our school during the summer, so I haven’t gotten a chance to put it on the CNC yet. I tested an older version which worked great, but not this one. Anyways, it holds extrusions reasonably well. Here’s the CAD, but I kinda goofed up. The bottom should be 1/2" thick and not 3/8" since that’s the length of the eccentric screws mitee 10204 comes with. So either the clamps stick out a bit or you need a 1/8" spacer plate between this and the omio.

BleepBloop:

you need a 1/8" spacer plate between this and the omio.

Two other alternatives:

  1. cut the length of the eccentric screws.
  2. Drill a hole in your waste board under the screw and let the extra screw length go into the hole. Might not be the best idea if you’re not using a waste board under your fixture.

Do not use with the head sticking up an 1/8". You’ll damage the hex and won’t achieve good clamping pressure.
